        "id": 5145
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-06T19:52:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Checks are triggered automatically by github when patches are uploaded. The job of the \"CQ\" (which I like to call poller here) is to watch for PRs with the label and then automatically merge them when they:\n\n* Have passed CI on their latest commit\n* Have at least one \"approve\" review\n* Have no change request reviews\n* Have no merge conflicts\n\n\nhttps://github.com/flutter/cocoon/pull/507 has the actual proposal.",
      "parentUuid": "a29282f8_28360e0d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 365,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 366,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "b131fa8c50d9592fe807aac8628727c7c90e4169",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1e300b4b_c4393572",
        "filename": "autoroll/go/codereview/roll.go",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 366,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-06T20:02:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is there any way we can extend that to behave similarly to TreeHugger?\n- \"poller\" acknowledges that it\u0027s seen the PR by setting some \"in progress\" label\n- \"poller\" sets a \"success\" or \"failure\" label when all of the checks have finished\n- The above are done regardless of whether the PR is going to be auto-merged after checks finish successfully",
      "parentUuid": "ab243d9e_102c0d9d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 365,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 366,
        "endChar": 33
      },
